caption: I arrive at this superb place once a month since I like the good air that is part of this restaurant. The team is extraordianrillyremarkably welcoming and skilfull. The service is very quick. Also, the food you eat is great. I visited more than once and I was never disappointed. The cost is honest. I highly suggest this restaurant to to all.
Excellent food and service!!!
Great patio seating with a fire pit and standing heaters. Good food. Good service.
Last went during a bottomless happy hour.  Food was a buffet style and average. Mimosa were okay but had to constantly track down the waiter for refills before our timeslot ran out
Nice atmosphere. Excellent food.
Food was excellent. So was the ambience.
Consistently great food and drinks!
This place obviously knows how to take care of their clients. Regularly with a very kind mindset. The food is conveniently priced, regularly tasty and clean.

Took my girlfriend here for our 6 month anniversary. Let me start by saying we both work in the industry and are servers. It took about 12 minutes before we were greeted at our table, wasn’t even our server. Checked my ID and told me I looked 13, mind you I’m 22. Server finally came around and seemed irritable. Upon delivery of our apps the food runner winked at my girlfriend. Only saving grace was the manager and the food. Overall poor experience, expect better for $30 plus entrees and Bethesda location.

First time trying Mario's and it was really good. I love Peruvian food. I've always tried Don Felix and in my opinion, they do taste the same. I can taste a little more spiciness with the green sauce here than Don Felix and I love it. I just don't like the wait and parking.
The steak was cooked perfect awesome experience
This place sure knows how to please their clients. Always with a nice mindset. The food is affordably priced, regularly flavorful and clean.
Excellent food, very friendly employees, constantly  awesome ambience. They charge reasonable rates and the food quality is awesome. 5 stars.

Dined here on Saturday, Sept. 5th for dinner. We were seated on the patio and the food was superb. Perhaps a bit salty, but overall fantastic. I am only giving 2 stars because the service lacked. Hostess was friendly and kind, but our server seemed miserable. He lacked basic server mannerisms e.g. monotone voice, attitude (when asked questions about menu items), did not check on us to see if we needed drink refills or to ask how our food was, and just unfriendly demeanor overall. My party agreed that he ruined the experience with his horrid etiquette which is a real shame because everything else was great, for the most part. Also, the men's bathroom smelled heavily of piss, but I would rather bear that odor than to have him as my server again.
Two words....Happy Hour

This is a pretty classy restaurant. If you're looking for meat or seafood, both selections are quality. Staff was very friendly, respectful of space and everyone was wearing a mask so during these times it felt pretty safe!

Ambiance is very classy and the staff are doing an amazing job of keeping strict distancing and as much indoor mask wearing as reasonable. Service was incredibly quick at 8:00 on a Saturday. Boyfriend's steak and my scallops were cooked perfectly. Calamari appetizer and my plate of scallops, chard, and mashed potatoes were WAY over-salted but I will return to try something else.
(Translated by Google) We are lustos, with exquisite food for all gystos !!!!  (Original) Estamos lustos,con comida exquisita para todos los gystos!!!!
Great food and flawless service!
Very good food. Expensive wine.
Service was great and the food was outstanding!
Great service and food
Wonderful place

We had our staff holiday party here. They were extremely accommodating. We actually stayed past their hours of operation and I had no clue because I didn't feel rushed. Blake was our waiter he was well informed. For starters I had the fried calamari I mean if you're going to do it don't count the calories. For dinner I had the ribeye which was lovely and the Mac and cheese with bacon. The bacon was absolutely one of the best types of bacon I've ever had. The ribeye was done well and full of flavor. For dessert the chocolate raspberry ice cream as well as the pecan pie were delicious as well. Needles to say I had to share all my leftovers with my Pomeranian Wally she would NOT budge from my bag. Guess her 3D profile said what my palette said which was it's decadent! Overall I was happy with the the ambiance the weight staff and the establishment in general. There's also a parking garage right next to it which is a major bonus.
Brunch and atmosphere was so good!
Amazing, I was in physical pain from my inability to stop eating

Had a nice steak here after a conference. Booked the table online which was simple enough. The staff were friendly and very helpful. They have a nice range of beers on offer. I highly recommend the 7 Locks IPA.
Great professional waiter service.
Nice place but pretty expensive.  Bar menu is much more reasonable, burger was very good.
Food quality 🔪

We were able to get a table for Valentine’s Day. We were sat immediately even though we were early for our reservation, our waiter Sam was attentive and helpful and all the supporting staff provided excellent service. The fried calamari was some of the best I’ve ever had. The veal chop special was cooked beautifully, as was the filet minion. We loved the cheddar biscuits so much we asked for thirds. Excellent cappuccino to round off the evening. Will absolutely be going back.
Great atmosphere, quality food and service.
Amazing food. Nice atmosphere. Good wines. On the pricey side but worth it
So good for brunch. Jasmine was outstanding and even helped me present a gift to my wife ❤️

The service and coffee was simply amazing! I'm not much of a steak eater so I can't comment on the steak, my whole table of 8 got steak and I got fish. I enjoyed it but preferred the old bay shrimp cocktail that we ordered as an appetizer.  A gentleman in our party who was not from Maryland said those were the best shrimp he had ever eaten. Being a Marylander, I think it's the old bay, not necessarily the shrip. However, it doesn't take away from the fact we were fighting over the last one.  Oysters were also very good and fresh.   Still, I think that cup of coffee with a biscotti just made a perfect meal!  If you like seafood, choose this place you will not be disappointed.

First time there ever. Sat at the bar on Superbowl Sunday. Not very busy (understandably). Our bartender was awesome (didn't get his name). Made us solid cocktails. I was most impressed with when ordering apps he let us know that one of the seafood dishes only came with 3 and that we should order something else if we wanted more filling apps added to our order , which we did. Got us Hanger steak special, and Filet that were cooked to specifications. Manager came and checked on us when the bartender stepped away for a minute as well. Appreciated that. Will definitely return. Small detail. Loved watching them lay out the silverware exactly the same way on the counter. Always impressed by that at restaurants.
Food is amazing!! Ambience is just right and the service staff is pleasant and accommodating. Great place to experience.  I highly recommend a visit.
The raw bar though... !!!

I celebrated my graduation yesterday in this great restaurant. I am glad to say that we passed a astonishing evening and the restaurant was certainly the reason for the successful gathering. The team  cooperated in a gorgeous way, the meals were tasty and my buddies were very  cheerful. We shall definitely visit again for more joyful events. Thank you very much.
Duck nachos🤤I'd drive from Germntown to make this an afternoon staple

Very good happy hour. And they even offer it during the day on Saturdays! I enjoyed my bourbon cocktail, the oysters were fresh and tasty and I liked the shrimp tacos. Nice ambiance and friendly bartenders. I will certainly be back.
The only vegan options here will be a modified salad (and maybe the soup du jour if you're lucky) but they do them well at least! Service was good.
Courteous staff and beautiful interior. Great food for a descent price.
Love this place! Excellent food and great service! Would definitely come back!

Lovely ambiance, excellent service. Watery drinks. Risotto mushy, scallops overdone. Caesar salad had thin, tasteless dressing, fried anchovies(!) - a new twist on an old salad perhaps? Spicy gumbo lacked...spiciness.  Bread was  over baked,  oily and burnt on the bottom.

Blacks Bar is one of the most consistent and quality establishments in Bethesda, where many businesses have come and gone during the past decades.  Close to parking and both nightlife and business locations during the day, this is the place you'll never be sorry you took clients, friends or relatives when in Bethesda, MD
Food was delicious and the service was wonderful.  Great place for a date night or a night out with friends.
Great Food...
Scallops are outstanding as is the filet
Delightful oysters
Beautiful place and their happy hour menu is pretty good

Good was good. But when we got their lots of empty tables. Was told reservation was required but if we could be done in 1.15 min. But that doesn't mean you don't come back for more drinks. Service wasn't good.  So much for visiting a new place to eat.
Great place 😍

Great for large parties
good food great service

Excellent as always.
Good cocktails.

A bit pricey but all the food was top notch. We started with clams and the charcuterie board before moving on to the main course, I had the Pork chop w/mac'n'cheese side & my co-worker had the prime rib.  Pork chop was perfectly done, juicy and tender. Mac was out of this world.
Great food. Nice place and atmosphere.
Food was delicious, our waitress Megan was awesome, I had a great time
This is a very fine restaurant bar. Sea food and meat are very tasty! Very welcoming staff.
Accommodating. Good mussels w broth.

Great happy hour ambience, nice food and drink options. Service is top notch too!

Tonight was a good night at Black's. Two of us had the scallops/prawns/clams risotto, and we were pleased with the variety of flavors and the care that had been given to cooking the individual ingredients properly. One had the veal and another had the cowgirl steak, and both pronounced them flavorful and perfectly cooked. The shrimp cocktail was a hit, as was the seasonal salad with blackberries and seeds. The service was cheerful, prompt and efficient. Once again Black's proved us correct in proclaiming it's consistency and quality.
Best oysters in town!!
Excellent Atlantic salmon and my wife had a very nice salad. Service was good in a pleasant surrounding.
Great food and excellent service. Would definitely recommend.
Menu very small the drink menu was bigger than the food menu
One of my go-to places in Bethesda when I'm looking for a "nice" place. Pricey, but you get the whole upscale dining experience. Food and service are good.
The food is amazing and the mix drink are on point. Real nice spot for dinner.
excellent happy hour. Get the watermelon martini and spiced asparagus. 👌
Best brunch in MoCo. Possibly best restaurant in MoCo. Amazing food. Amazing service. Wonderful atmosphere and decor. Perfect dining experience from start to finish.
This place is awesome hands down. Staff, food, drinks and the crowd. I had a wonderful time and have never been let down by this place. A+

Thoroughly enjoyed the food and service at Black's Bethesda. The service was excellent, friendly, attentive, and helpful- from the busboy who helped getting us menus and water and ultimately boxing up our food, to the friendly and accommodating waiter, to the wine manager who helped me pick a delightful glass of Shiraz. The steak flatbread of the day was delicious, the old bay shrimp cocktail was cold, spicy, and peeled and very good. The scallops with crawfish butter and creamy potatoes were top-notch. The blue cheese on the burger was abundant, creamy and very tasty! Keep up the great service, it is appreciated and will have us come back!
Not enough vegan options for the Sunday buffet, but a nice resturaunt.
It's okay

Had an absolutely amazing dinner here. Everything we had from appetizers to entree to dessert was perfectly done and I couldn't have asked for better service, they were phenomenal. Will definitely be going back!

Took my wife for her bday, as it is one of her favorites. The outdoor seating is nice in the spring, and the bar area has a few TVs but they don't overwhelm the place or make you feel like you're in a sports bar. So while the place is upscale, it's not too stuffy and you can spend an evening there.  Highly recommend the Black's Burger!
Overpriced for what you get on the plate. Great sommelier on the night, though, with some fine half-price specials on selected bottles.
Excellent gumbo and fancy dessert of the day!
Wonderful food.
Great brunch that includes prime rib and a very nice raw bar.
Great options for oysters. Odd that we.cpuld not get myltiple bottles of the same wine. Supply chain management?
Great streak and a solid old fashioned.

Their brunch is one of the best in the area. Drinks are tasty and the raw bar items are fresh. The desserts are very rich and filling so resist the temptation and wait until the end for desserts. Staff was very attentive and friendly.
Went to happy hour. Food was ok, but drinks were sub par. Service was good.
Amazing pan sear salmon
Best oysters around. Go during happy hour!
Simply the best restaurant in Bethesda
Excellent seafood stew and scallops. Avoid the Caesar salad. Attentive service.
As always, great food, great service!
I definitely want to go back here.  They have some of the more unique cocktails I’ve seen in the DC area. One of their drinks has duck fat bourbon and believe it or not, it rocks.
Great aesthetic, excellent service, delicious food. On the pricy side, but I've honestly never had a better pork chop in my life.

While the food was amazing, the service was NOT, by our primary server Brett, and the other server that asked us how we were seated, if we had made a reservation or just walked in after being seated already for 30 minutes. From the moment we were seated he was racially profiling my friends and I. He made it known by his actions and failure to provide us with good service as he did the other patrons. The bussers were amazing and on point. Celebrating my birthday, and having to experience this.  I would NEVER go back if it was based on service alone.. but the food is 5 star quality. The desserts were ok not 5 star, but my mug was broken on the inside and out that served my fogato. Hope they get better servers that appreciate the variety of patrons that come in and have to waste their hard earned money on such ignorant behavior.

Came here for happy hour on a rainy Saturday night. Warm and cozy atmosphere & friendly service. Enjoyed the oysters and the kitchen was kind enough to split the seafood stew for us. Will certainly be back.
Delish

I truly cannot complain about anything at Black's, but I feel 5 stars would not be a fair grade. It was Monday night. We were the first to sit down in the dining room. Food was amazing: oysters, charcuterie, risotto with filet, Berkshire Pork chop and gnocchi. Ridiculously delicious. Service, good... couldn't tell you his name. Wine, divine.
Really good food, great service.
Great Raw Bar brunch option! Oysters for days!
very exquisite

Expensive food which is over seasoned and over salted to hide average grade ingredients. Oysters are often low quality, and again over priced. At this location, you're basically paying for the Bethesda's faux luxury tax. A cup of black coffee should not cost $5 at an oyster bar.
A Bethesda stand by.  After all these years, the food and service stand above the rest.  Whether in the bar or dining room, they have some of the best seafood around.
Great food and service.

Good was very good, especially the mussels. Definitely goes on my list of places to bring visiting family.
Best Burger in Bethesda. Fantastic oyster menu too. Charcuterie plate is phenomenal. And that's just the easy menu. It's probably the best fine dining experience one can have in Bethesda.

Went here for happy hour and only ordered off the happy hour menu. We ordered two different cocktails- a greyhound and a burnt orange bourbon drink. Both were a bit light in the liquor area but drinkable. The duck nachos were good but pretty much only tasted like BBQ sauce and the grilled calamari was enjoyable. We will probably return as it is hard to find cocktails on happy hour in Bethesda.
Very good food, service, and drinks.  Highly recommend
Ooooohh! Niiiice! Celebrated a friend's birthday here. The service was great, friendly staff who managed to remain available without hovering. I absolutely love that! And the fooood!!! On point!
Brunch is amazing. Highly recommend. A bit pricey but worth it.
Excellent food, quick service, beautiful atmosphere!!

Came here for a department holiday party. The food was good and straightforward, but the service wasn't too good. Many enjoyed their dishes. I had the Caeser salad with chicken and the mushroom soup and house red wine. The wine was good, but the soup portion was quite small, as was the salad. It was the pick three selection. They did overcook one dish, but they were likely rushed. The bread was tasty and the mussels we're good. Definitely beware that you need to clearly specify how you want your food cooked (medium vs well done) and if you want your food spicy. They over cooked or under cooked a few dishes or added too much spice.
A great lunch, best burgers in the area!
Good lunch. Was oddly packed for a wednesday.  Had to ask server 4 tines for milk and sugar for tea.  And 3 tines for utensils.

Went for a lunch meeting and was a perfect place for that as space was big enough and also not loud. I had the risotto special with was very good. The service was very attentive but also we were not rushed. I would def come back here again.
Always great food, great company, and great atmosphere.
Great atmosphere  seafood & music was live an fresh

We have been here four or five times over the last couple of years. The food is always delicious. The service is usually pretty good, and there are some characters amongst the wait staff. But, there is no vibe in this restaurant anymore. Sitting outside isn't bad, but the inside dining room has no energy. Actually, it's just boring, but the menu options can make it work.

First time dining at Black's Bar & Kitchen for dinner and it was OUTSTANDING. I've visited once for brunch and that was also OUTSTANDING. However, OUTSTANDING is the food and atmosphere...this is not a cheap experience.  I've had Duck Confit and Riesling at several different restaurants, but this night was the best savory flavor and wine I've experienced. Definitely worth the pricey bill. I'll visit again, but on special occasions. I also recommend, reserving a table on Open table.

Went for happy hour, drinks are quality and prices are reasonable. Happy hour food menu is also amazing. We enjoyed the calamari, the duck nachos 😋, and the Thai mussels 😋 very tasty... would go to their happy hour again
Found it uncomfortably noisy. Food was ok for the most part, but things seemed underseasoned - even an apple pie dessert. Prices are very high. Good service.

Love wines by the glass, premium oysters floating in their own juices & the comfort of meeting a blind date in a lively but not-so-noisy bar.  My fav dish: Thai Oysters, perfect blend of savvy, delice sauce with benign jalapeno peppers & bread for dunking!  It's pricey but I think worth it!

Upscale restaurant with a great menu. Comprehensive wine list. We started off with the Thai mussels and let's just say I'd go back just for these. So delicious, I cleaned up the bowl pretty well. Hubby had the Whole Bronizo which he thoroughly enjoyed; the thyme used to stuff the fish gives it a great taste. I had the Grilled Hanger Steak and it was cooked just right, I enjoyed it. The service was so-so, the waitress was not as fast as we'd have liked especially in checking out. You can make a reservation or walk in. The interior is beautiful too. I'll be back.
The food is actually good, but their drinks? meh!
Always good. Service can be hit or miss, but compared to Woodmont across the street it's a no brainer. Stick to the oysters and seafood. The premier black salts are really good!
Great food, buffet is amazing as always.
Great food, nice selections, nice ambiance, friendly staff, I enjoyed their wines selections. Fabulous seafood restaurant, oysters fresh etc .

Nestled in the heart of downtown Brthesda, BBK has great food and lots of TVs for the  perfect sport watching setting! The old bay crab dip, philly cheesesteak, Korean bbq tacos and chocolate chip cookie monster sandwich were all AMAZING!

I love Blacks.  They tried to give me the wrong year on the bottle of Sancerre, and when I sent it back...the sommelier tried to explain what a Sancerre is.  Lol.  He did not seem to understand the year was wrong.  But otherwise great food

Don't miss the corn bread with honey butter. Full bar and solid wine list should get you what you want on the beverage front. It is expensive,  so plan on taking your time and enjoy yourself. It can be casual or dressy depending on your mood.
